<div class="no_qual_main_page container">

<div class = "sorry col-md-12 text-center">
	<h1> Sorry, unfortunately you do not qualify </h1>
</div>

<div class = "sorry col-md-12 text-center" >
	<h2> Please check out your stats below to see why you didn't qualify</h2>
</div>

<div class = "dti col-md-12 text-center">
		<div class = "noq1 col-md-4" >
			<h2> Total Debt = $<%= "#{@total_debt}" %> </h2>
		</div>
		
		<div class = "noq2 col-md-4" >
			<h2> Total Income = $<%= "#{@total_income}" %> </h2>
		</div>

		<div class = "noq3 col-md-4">
			<h2> DTI = <%= "#{@dti}" %> </h2>
		</div>
		
		<div class = "noq4 col-md-12 text-center">
			<h3> Typical Debt To Income (DTI) ratios need to be around 0.43. Your's is currently at <%= "#{@dti}" %> </h3>
		</div>
	</div>

<div class = "dti col-md-12 text-center">	
		<div class = "noq5">
			<h2> Total Loan To Value = <%= "#{@ltv}" %> </h2>
		</div>

		<div class = "noq6">
			<h3> Most banks will allow for a range of LTVs when making a qualification decision. Typically, any LTV above .8 will require mortgage insurance. Often times in order to qualify for mortgage insurance you need to meet even stricter guidelines. If you need a loan amount that puts your LTV higher than .8, consult with your local lender about the requirements for obtaining mortgage insurance.</h3>
		</div>
</div>

<div class = "dti col-md-12 text-center">	
		<div class = "noq7">
			<h2> Credit Score = <%= "#{@credit_score}" %> </h2>
		</div>

		<div class = "noq8">
			<h3> Your current credit score is <%= "#{@credit_score}" %>. Most banks will accept a minimum credit score of 640 or greater when determing whether or not a borrower can qualify. As a general rule of thumb, if your credit score is 740 or better, you wont need to worry about your credit score as a mitigating factor to the bank.</h3>
		</div>
</div>

<div class = "dti col-md-12 text-center">
		<div class = "noq9">
			<h2> Length of Employment = <%= "#{@employment_length}" %> </h2>
		</div>
	
		<div class = "noq10">
			<h3>Most inverstors will require a 2 year employmnet history. Even if you have switched jobs recently, you may be able to argue that you have been in the same industry for 2 or more years. Additionally, you may be able to qualify with less than 2 years of employment, but that will be up to the specific lending institution.</h3>	
		</div>
	</div>
</div>